ificate of incorporation, trade license)\\n6. recent utility bills as proof of business address\\n7. bank statements for the past six months\\n8. income tax returns for the past two years\\n9. any other documents as required by the bank based on the nature of the business and the loan amount\\n\\nIt's essential to check the specific requirements with Global IME Bank or the Nepal Rastra Bank for the most accurate and up-to-date information on working capital guidelines and documentation requirements."}, "sources": [{"object": "context.chunk", "score": 0.698219439909658, "document": {"object": "ingest.document", "doc_id": "e1cb2a4f-6b47-4a90-b744-2086c97ef221", "doc_metadata": {"window": "Global IME Bank Limited  AML / CFT Policy \\n15 e. Downstream Correspondent Banking (Nested Account): The Bank shall not allow \\ndownstream correspondent banking service and nested account activities to other \\nfinancial institutions. \\n \\n f. Payable-through Accounts or Pass-through Accounts \\nThe Bank shall not allow its customers to directly access the correspondent account to \\nconduct business on their own behalf.  \\n \\n g. Use of personal accounts for business purposes \\nThe Bank shall discourage use of personal saving accounts to be used for business \\npurposes.   \\n 3.2 Reporting \\n3.2.1 Resubmission Policy   \\nBank shall not attempt to resubmit any transaction that has already been rejected \\ndue to the concern over Sanctions or ML/TF. ", "original_text": "Global IME Bank Limited  AML / CFT Policy \\n15 e. Downstream Correspondent Banking (Nested Account): The Bank shall not allow \\ndownstream correspondent banking service and nested account activities to other \\nfinancial institutions. \\n \\n", "page_label": "21", "file_name": "AML CFT POLICY 2023.pdf", "doc_id": "e1cb2a4f-6b47-4a90-b744-2086c97ef221"}}, "text": "Global IME Bank Limited  AML / CFT Policy \\n15 e. Downstream Correspondent Banking (Nested Account): The Bank shall not allow \\ndownstream corre