ation numbers, amounts, and any fees or charges associated with the transaction.\\n7. Record-keeping: Both the sender and recipient banks should maintain accurate records of all SWIFT messages and transactions for compliance purposes. This may include retaining copies of messages, transaction logs, and any related documentation.\\n\\nBy following these rules and procedures, banks can ensure that their SWIFT transactions are secure, accurate, and compliant with regulatory requirements."}, "sources": [{"object": "context.chunk", "score": 0.6140198273485482, "document": {"object": "ingest.document", "doc_id": "d8e72576-6231-40d1-a1ab-9a9111f8e956", "doc_metadata": {"window": "Reaord the detail of SWFT\\nmessaSe in a re8isler.  Eranch shall mention the Tran lD, reference number and details of amount\\ntransfened and commission charged to the customer in the SWIFTapplication form.The customercopy\\nof the applicetion form duly signed and marked with bank stamp should b\\u20ac provided to the\\ncustomer/applicant.\\n E. Ihe SwlFTmessa8e should besiSned by two authorized peGons as perthe signine authority mentioned\\nin Lirt of Authoriz\\u20acd Sitnatures ofth\\u20ac Bank.  Th\\u20ac sitned SWIFT message should b\\u20ac forwarded to SwlFT\\n0epartment within the stipulated time.\\n G,F, SWTFT Department on receipt of branch requert, shall route the message and forward a copy of SWFT\\nmesrage to the concerned branch.\\n mitted copy is reaeived from SWIFT Depa(menl branch should check and verify\\nessage was transmitted so thatthe errorcan be rectlfled in timewllhout any delay,\\nssaSe should be kept alongwith the applicition and doorments in the file.After the SWIFT trans\\nwhetherthe cofied m\\nIhe copy of XIFT me\\nry 71A", "original_text": "Th\\u20ac sitned SWIFT message should b\\u20ac forwarded to SwlFT\\n0epartment within the stipulated time.\\n", "page_label": "77", "file_name": "Unified Branch Operations Manual.pdf", "doc_id": "d8e72576-6231-40d1-a1ab-9a9111f8e956"