 system, MICR encoding system, and other relevant systems to ensure smooth processing of cheques.\\n8. Monitor and maintain the system: Regularly monitor the system for any errors, discrepancies, or fraudulent activities. Maintain the system by updating software, hardware, and security measures as needed.\\n\\nBy automating the inward cheque clearance process, you can reduce manual intervention, improve efficiency, and ensure faster processing of cheques."}, "sources": [{"object": "context.chunk", "score": 0.6453042364802387, "document": {"object": "ingest.document", "doc_id": "ed43bc06-1189-44de-b1c6-c46ae1971f6b", "doc_metadata": {"window": "UotPd Brcnch Operotiont Monuol\\n3.4 Paymentol lnte.en and P.hclpal\\n3.4.1 Paymrnt oI lnteaen\\nA. The lntereston flred depositshallbe paid ina re8ul.rtime intedalorat maturity as per agre\\u20acd te.ms at\\nthe time of opening the account and as p\\u20acr the f\\u20acatuips of the d\\u20acposir product.  System shatt\\nautomatlcally accrue interest for the d\\u20acposit amount and credit in the checkin&/nominee account ofthe\\naccount holder period ically as perdetails and instructron reconded in the rystem\\ng. The lnterestwlllbe pald inthenomrnee account at the time ofinterest payment.\\n 3.4.2 P.ym\\u20acnt of Principal\\nA. The payment of prhcipalamount should be made on maturity ofthe flred deposit.  Paym\\u20acnt of principat\\namount shall be made by the branch only from where the account is maintained, tn case the maturity\\ndate fulls ln a holiday, the principal amount should be paid in the n\\u20acxtworkintday.\\n B. Paymentofth\\u20ac principalamount ofthe fixed deposit shonld be mad\\u20ac to the account holderonly through\\naccounttransf\\u20acr.\\n", "original_text": "System shatt\\nautomatlcally accrue interest for the d\\u20acposit amount and credit in the checkin&/nominee account ofthe\\naccount holder period ically as perdetails and instructron reconded in the rystem\\ng. The lnterestwlllbe pald inthenomrne