968	assistant	{"id": "504d7a23-ee64-40a0-b887-14570204b4b6", "object": "completion", "created": 1713698888, "model": "private-gpt", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "delta": null, "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": "Video KYC, also known as Video-Based KYC or Video-Based Customer Identification Process, is an alternative method for verifying the identity of customers using video conferencing technology. This method allows banks, financial institutions, and other regulated entities to onboard new customers or update existing customers' information in a secure, remote, and efficient manner.\\n\\nVideo KYC typically involves the following steps:\\n\\n1. Scheduling: The customer schedules a video call with the bank or financial institution's representative, usually through an online portal or mobile application.\\n\\n2. Identity verification: During the video call, the representative asks the customer to present their identity documents, such as a passport, driver's license, or national ID card, for visual inspection. The representative may also ask the customer to perform actions that confirm their identity, such as providing their date of birth or answering security questions.\\n\\n3. Data capture: The representative captures a clear image of the identity documents and records the video call for future reference. This video recording serves as an additional layer of security and can be used in case of disputes or investigations.\\n\\n4. Documentation: The bank or financial institution stores the captured data, including the video recording, in their secure systems for compliance purposes. This data may be used for future reference or audits by regulatory authorities.\\n\\n5. Compliance: Video KYC follows the same regulatory requirements as traditional KYC processes, ensuring that the customer's identity is verified in accordance with Anti-Money Laundering (AML) and Combating the Financing of Terrorism (CFT) guidelines.\\n\\nBenefits of Video KYC:\\n\\n* 