mmunication and public engagement: Engaging with local communities, stakeholders, and the media to communicate provincial policies and initiatives, as well as to gather feedback and input on local needs and concerns.\\n10. Crisis management: Leading the province's response to natural disasters, public health emergencies, or other crises, ensuring that resources are allocated effectively and that the needs of affected communities are addressed."}, "sources": [{"object": "context.chunk", "score": 0.5922930253892904, "document": {"object": "ingest.document", "doc_id": "d2dd8737-2efd-4908-8fc2-697e11ba48f9", "doc_metadata": {"window": "ol C.sh Umlt\\nA. Branch should normally hold thecash balance sufficient Ior carryinB ou t theirdatty transections\\nD. Branch Operations oepartment shallmonitor on daily basE tharthe totatcash batance of att branches ts\\nunderthe vault limit and shall lnstruct the branches for manaSement of the excess fund.\\n B. There must be two panels/groups (\\"A\\" and \\"8\\" panel) amongst the vault custodians ln the Branch to\\nhandle keys of the veult.  The vault custodia ns in each panel/Brou p shall hand le on ly one set of keys at a\\ntime.Approving autho.ily forvaull key assignment will be as per Approving Authority Matrix.\\n C. The Main custodian shall be call\\u20acd \\"Primary Xey Holde/.  Similady, branch shall nominate alternate staff\\nas alternate key holderls)in the prescribed format.lfthe key holders/vault custodians are required to b\\u20ac\\nchanted, prior approvalshould bE taken from concerned authority.ln abrence ofPrimary Key Holder or\\ninability to hold key by the Prlmary Key holder, the alternate key holder shallhandle thevaultl(eys.8.  Tell\\u20acr should normally hold the c:sh balance sufficienr to cirry out reSutar transaction.  tn excep onat\\ncases llke bulk cash deposits, the cash rn the counter should be manag\\u20acd soon after compl\\u20acrion of the\\npartlcular tranraction. ", "original_text": "C. The Main custo